---
const repoUrl = 'https://github.com/acoyfellow/flue-snippets';
---

<section class="hero">
  <h1>Flue on Cloudflare</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    I wanted to see what it actually looks like to build agents with
    <a href="https://flueframework.com">Flue</a> on Cloudflare Workers. Turns out the answer
    is mostly: less code than I expected. Four agents I built, smallest to largest.
  </p>
  <p class="meta muted">
    Every snippet really deploys to a real Worker. Around $0.0001 per run, the e2e
    destroys the Worker after it asserts.
    <a href={repoUrl}>Repo →</a>
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--text);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .meta {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
